t:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The regional structure of OFSTED and Schools Commissioners may provide the structure between schools and the Secretary of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">State. However, it is imperative that this is light-touch and not bureaucratic, working in a transparent and cost-effective way and leaving successful schools to get on with it.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 24pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.29pt; orphans:0; padding-left:3.71pt; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What role academy chains play or should play in the new school landscape; how</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> accountable they are; and what issues they raise with regard to governance arrangements;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">5.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">There is a place for chains but</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> there should be a limit on the size and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">their </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">geographical spread.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">5.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Small local chains are the best model as the ability </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">to work</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> across schools, to share a common ethos and to move staff around is enhanced by proximity.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">5.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">OFSTED MUST inspect chains as well as individual schools. They must look at what being in a chain adds in terms of performance and take action if a chain is underp</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">erforming or failing to address weaknesses in a member school.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 16pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">5.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Governance is an issue across the system and not just in chains. The move from a stakeholder model to a skills-based form of Governance needs to be hastened. Better training for Governors and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">a more robust selection of the chair needs to be implemented.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 16pt; orphans: